      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I need help writing a rejection email. We had a candidate, Marcus, who made it all the way to the final interview for our Senior Dev role here in Austin. He's really talented and had great technical skills, but we decided to go with someone who had a bit more experience with our specific cloud architecture. I want the email to be professional and kind because he was a great guy, but we need to be firm that the decision is final. Can you draft something?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Your Application for the Senior Dev Role\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I wanted to extend my sincerest gratitude for your interest in the Senior Dev role with our Austin-based team. Your passion for technology and your impressive technical skills were evident throughout the interview process, and we truly appreciate the time you invested in sharing your vision and experiences with us.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience aligns more closely with our specific cloud architecture needs. This decision was not easy, as you are undoubtedly a talented individual with a bright future ahead of you.\n\nWe understand that this news may be disappointing, and we want to assure you that this decision was made with the company's best interests in mind. We hope you will not be discouraged and will continue to pursue your professional goals with the same enthusiasm and dedication that you have shown us.\n\nThank you once again for your interest in our company and for your understanding. We wish you all the best in your future endeavors.\n\nWarm regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Position]\n[Company Name]",
